==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Phase displacement
<hw>Phase displacement</hw>. <fld>(Elec.)</fld> <def>A charge of phase
whereby an alternating current attains its maximum later or earlier. An
inductance would cause a lag, a capacity would cause an advance, in
phase.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Phase in</ent>⟦br⟧
